CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1784321281
OL,3,CTemperatures above 30C for 12th day in
OL,4,Ca row as heatwave continues
OL,6,FThere have now been 27 days in 2026,
OL,7,Fconsecutive and non-consecutive, when
OL,8,F30C has been exceeded somewhere in the
OL,9,FUK: seven in May, eight in June and 12
OL,10,Fin July.
OL,12,FThe record for the number of 30C-plus
OL,13,Fdays in a calendar year is 34, which
OL,14,Fwas set in 1995.
OL,16,FThis weekend will see plenty of
OL,17,Fsunshine and dry weather, although
OL,18,Fthere may be a few isolated showers
OL,19,Fand a dip in temperatures.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1784321281
OL,3,CTemperatures above 30C for 12th day in
OL,4,Ca row as heatwave continues
OL,6,FOvercast conditions are also forecast
OL,7,Fin many regions, which will bring
OL,8,Ftemperatures down.
OL,10,FIt is too soon to say whether the
OL,11,Fheatwave conditions will last beyond
OL,12,Fthe next 10 days and towards the end
OL,13,Fof July.
OL,15,FDespite this, no significant rain is
OL,16,Fforecast in the near future, putting
OL,17,Fincreasing pressure on the country's
OL,18,Fwater supply.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
