CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1784321281
OL,3,CTemperatures above 30C for 12th day in
OL,4,Ca row as heatwave continues
OL,6,FThe Met Office said Wales is sitting
OL,7,F2.2C above an average of around 19.3C,
OL,8,Fand while Scotland and Northern
OL,9,FIreland have remained closer to their
OL,10,Fseasonal norms of 17.3C and 18.6C,
OL,11,Fthey are still running above average
OL,12,Fat 0.9C and 1.3C respectively.
OL,14,FEarlier this month, researchers from
OL,15,FImperial College London, the Met
OL,16,FOffice, and the London School of
OL,17,FHygiene and Tropical Medicine (LSHTM)
OL,18,Fwarned that the UK's prolonged period
OL,19,Fof extreme heat in 2026 has caused at
OL,20,Fleast 2,700 deaths.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1784321281
OL,3,CTemperatures above 30C for 12th day in
OL,4,Ca row as heatwave continues
OL,6,FMore than two fifths (42%) of the
OL,7,F2,700 deaths were a result of the
OL,8,Fextra heat caused by human activity `
OL,9,Fmostly burning fossil fuels, they
OL,10,Ffound.
OL,12,FTheir study examined the periods
OL,13,Faround the record-breaking heatwaves
OL,14,Fof May, when temperatures peaked at
OL,15,F35.1C, and June, which hit new highs
OL,16,Ffor the month of above 37C,
OL,17,Faccompanied by high humidity.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1784321281
OL,3,CTemperatures above 30C for 12th day in
OL,4,Ca row as heatwave continues
OL,6,FThe analysis found that about 550
OL,7,Fpeople are estimated to have died
OL,8,Fbecause of heat-related causes in nine
OL,9,Fdays of the May heatwave, and about
OL,10,F2,200 in the 11 days around the June
OL,11,Fheatwave in England and Wales.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/8
